The way Confluence resolves a Content instance into a URL cannot be influenced by plugins.

Its a relatively static code path that really only works if you are storing Pages as Pages(*\).  I want a plugin point that allows me to generate a different url based on some logic.

The process should be, given wiki markup like this:

{noformat}[page link]{noformat}

Have a {{ContentUrlManager}} go through a sorted series of {{ContentResolvers}} to see which one can resolve the link.  The default resolver will do the normal process of trying to resolve it into a name, and producing a html link to the view or creation of a new page.

Open this up as a pluigin point and you can create new resolvers that could generate a different url based on things inside the page such as properties in the property set.

(*\) I want to be able to store "other" data in Content Entity Objects and give it meaning other than just a "page of content"

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
