When filtering a search by author the hits shown for the search do not indicate anything about the author or contributor for each hit. This impairs the users trust of the filter. Perhaps it would be good to show a field along the lines of 'created by' or 'modified by' beside each match.

To go a step further, author filtering will match a document if the author entered made any change to any version. e.g. cmonger changed version 3 only of a document that is now at version 25. Even when clicking on the hit it may not be obvious why this document has matched. Could we extend the display on the hit list with something like 'version 3 edited by cmonger'? At present this would mean a version look up in the DB which we may want to avoid.

Alternative thinking could be to only record a particular editor as a contributor if they changed more than x% of the document etc.

